The paper proposes a framework for evaluating clustering algorithms, which is a common topic in machine learning and data science. The use of bipartite graphs and normalization techniques suggests a focus on clustering evaluation measures, which are commonly studied in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of feature vectors and pairwise distances also suggests a focus on data analysis and clustering algorithms, which are studied in subfields such as natural language processing (cs.CL), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computer vision (cs.CV).
